00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
 Social networking sites are used by 1/3 people around the world 

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:06.230
 They have had a great impact on society 

00:00:06.230 --> 00:00:08.020
 But what about our bodies? 

00:00:08.020 --> 00:00:10.740
 Here are 5 ways of social networking and the Internet 

00:00:10.740 --> 00:00:12.540
 Influence your mind at the moment 

00:00:12.540 --> 00:00:13.730
 Can not you stop? 

00:00:13.730 --> 00:00:16.070
 It is surprising that 5-10% of Internet users 

00:00:16.070 --> 00:00:19.280
 Are not actually able to control the amount of time they spend online. 

00:00:19.280 --> 00:00:22.470
 Although it is self-addiction and not drug addiction, 

00:00:22.470 --> 00:00:23.730
 Examine the brains of these people 

00:00:23.769 --> 00:00:27.669
 Revealed weakness in areas similar to those of drug addicts. 

00:00:27.669 --> 00:00:30.469
 Specifically, there is a clear decline of white matter in 

00:00:30.469 --> 00:00:33.779
 Areas that control emotions, attention and decision making. 

00:00:33.779 --> 00:00:37.519
 Because social media provide immediate rewards for little effort, 

00:00:37.519 --> 00:00:41.189
 Your mind begins to re-install itself, so you want these stimuli, 

00:00:41.189 --> 00:00:45.279
 As you begin to want more of these neurological excitements after each reaction. 

00:00:45.279 --> 00:00:47.619
 Looks like drugs. Is not it? 

00:00:47.619 --> 00:00:49.809
 We also see a change when we look at multitasking. 

00:00:49.809 --> 00:00:52.219
 You may think that those who use social media 

00:00:52.219 --> 00:00:54.109
 Or permanently switch between work and websites 

00:00:54.109 --> 00:00:55.199
 They are best at multitasking, 

00:00:55.199 --> 00:00:58.649
 But studies revealed that when compared to those who use the means of communication frequently to others, 

00:00:58.649 --> 00:01:01.499
 Their performance is much worse during task switching tests. 

00:01:01.499 --> 00:01:06.009
 Increasing online multitasking reduces your brain's ability to filter out overlaps, 

00:01:06.009 --> 00:01:09.509
 It can even make it harder for your mind to learn information in a way that you can remember 

00:01:09.509 --> 00:01:12.089
 Like your phone rings in the middle of a product. 

00:01:12.089 --> 00:01:14.309
 Or wait .. Is it really Ren ?? 

